            "command": "gh issue create --title \"hardening: rate-limit /api/v1/identity endpoint\" --body \"$(cat <<'EOF'\n## Problem\n\nThe `/api/v1/identity` endpoint is intentionally public (unauthenticated LAN peers need it for discovery verification), but it has no rate limiting. An attacker can spam challenge-response requests.\n\nThe \"signature oracle\" risk is low — the signed payload uses a domain-specific prefix (`reme-identity-v1:`) and includes the node's public key, making signatures unusable outside this protocol. Rate limiting is a hardening measure.\n\n## Fix\n\nAdd an IP-based rate limiter (e.g., 10 req/s per IP) to the identity endpoint, similar to existing `submit_ip` / `fetch_ip` limiters in `rate_limit.rs`.\n\n## References\n\n- `apps/node/src/api.rs:93` — public route declaration\n- `apps/node/src/api.rs:878` — handler\n- `apps/node/src/rate_limit.rs` — existing limiter infrastructure\nEOF\n)\" --label \"security\"",
